}}'''Samoa''' is a [[Nations|country]] that was added to [[BitLife: Life Simulator|BitLife]] in July 10, 2022. Its default cities only include the capital, Apia.

On July 10, 2022, new countries were added to both iOS and Android. Along with Samoa, there was also [[Andorra]], [[Angola]], [[Aruba]], [[Belize]], [[El Salvador]], [[Guatemala]], [[Guyana]], [[Haiti]], [[Nicaragua]], [[Papua New Guinea]], [[Paraguay]], [[Tunisia]], and [[Uganda]]. This was added in a bug fix update prior to the upcoming Business Update.

Since it's inclusion of the game, the '''Independent State of Samoa''' is one of the nations where the '''<u>player cannot start a political career</u>''', despite being a Unitary Parliamentary Republic, it hasn't been explained why but possibly the developers simply forgot to add the special career. 

